{
  "buggy_files": ["fs/nfs/nfs3proc.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["nfs3_rpc_wrapper"],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The nfs3_rpc_wrapper function (lines 30-42) has a critical bug at line 39 where it unconditionally sets 'res = -ERESTARTSYS' after sleeping for a JUKEBOX retry, even when NO fatal signal has been detected. This differs from the correct pattern in nfs4proc.c which only sets ERESTARTSYS if 'fatal_signal_pending(current)' is true. When getattr is called during autofs mount point revalidation and receives EJUKEBOX, the wrapper incorrectly returns ERESTARTSYS even for normal timeout conditions without signals. This causes nfs_revalidate_inode to fail, triggering nfs_lookup_revalidate to invalidate the autofs mount point dentry (via out_zap_parent), causing the entire mount to disappear. The tcpdump showing successful server replies but client receiving -512 error confirms this - the wrapper is incorrectly setting the error before the RPC layer can process successful replies. The fix is to only set 'res = -ERESTARTSYS' when a fatal signal is actually detected, matching the pattern used in nfs4_delay() in nfs4proc.c lines 120-127."
}

